caption: I had a Birthday dinner here Everything was great including the drinks ! We got our food fast definitely was not a long wait for anything.

My daughter and I happened upon this quaint little Caribbean Restaurant for lunch and enjoyed the island taste very much‼️ The spice was just right and the service was fabulous...thanks Joseph❣️ The atmosphere and artwork also made for a very happy experience😊👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻
Super cool spot, they have a great little space to read and have a drink. I really appreciated Joseph and the cooks for accommodating me with my health concerns. Definitely come check it out guys!
Excellent! The service on a busy Saturday was great and the food was exquisite. Definitely will go back!
Food and service absolutely wonderful!!!
No need to leave Jacksonville, no need to book a flight to the island to get GREAT Caribbean food! Pink Salt was absolutely amazing! Our waiter JoJo took great care of me and my wife!!
Love the menu, great ambiance.

Not a new restaurant but a new location well thought out and very attractive. Ask for Joseph to be your server. Very professional and engaging. High marks for staff. The food which is inspired by the cuisine of Jamaica is wonderful. We had the Pink Salt sandwich and jerk shrimp bowl (spicy) both of which were delicious. If you haven't been, Go! You won't regret it.
Nice classy environment 👏 great customer service. Just make sure you have reservations prior to arrival there's a possibility you will not eat if you don't 😉.
Food and service was excellent!!!
Absolutely loved brunch today! We had an awesome waiter, JoJo!  He tended to our every need. Our meals were delicious! I am a forever patron of Pink Salt!
Chef Richards is high on our list of favorites. His dishes are creative and authentic. If you are looking for a true Carribean food experience this is the place. Bring your appetite.
Best restaurant ever. Extremely flavorful food. Great customer service. Amazing dinner menu options for date night. 😊 💕
Really great vibe, good people, spectacular food & drink. Will be back to try everything on the menu!
The food was amazing and our waiter Joseph was awesome!!

We tried this place on a whim and the food was amazing!  I expected some decent food but I was blown away by the layers of flavor.  I had the Island Style Short Ribs and my wife had the Coconut Curry Shrimp.  Both meals far exceeded our expectations and I highly recommend either dish.  We just found our new favorite place to eat.  I loved the atmosphere as well.  If I could give this restaurant more stars I would.
Absolutely amazing food!!! The Gumbo over the grits, WOW 🔥. Joseph the waiter was great!! We WILL be back 👍🏾
Love the location and the food was great! Came with my daughters for brunch. We ordered the Shrimp Po Boy,  Salmon Benedict and Jumbo Gumbo.  JoJo was our server  and he was an excellent host!
Amazing food!!!!!!

I should have taken pics of the food but my mouth was watering so bad I forgot! The food was amazing! Went to Pink Salt today with 2 coworkers for my birthday and it did not disappoint! From the flavorful complimentary crawfish soup to the best Gumbo I've ever eaten woth tender chunks of fish, shrimp and scallops, to the bright, buttery Chardonnay Jojo picked for me, the meal was spectacular.  The space is bright, airy and fresh with gorgeous pops of color throughout.  I'll definitely be back!
Jojo was amazing... thank you. The food was delicious, the atmosphere was inviting, and service was stellar. Great spot for office meetings or small church meetings. I WILL be back!

Pink Salt will always one of my favorites🖤  Friends treated me to a birthday dinner here  when I turned 50 and I can't stop coming back!!  The new location is beautiful (I'm partial to the old location in Baymeadows because it was near me 😜)  Today I tried the curry chicken bowl and they did not disappoint!!!  I love it😋  My server Joseph has the best customer service EVER!!

I would give this place more stars if there was an option.  The food was incredible.  We had Coconut Curry Shrimp, the Salmon, Oxtail Stew, Braised Rabbit and the Island Style Short Ribs.  ALL of it was amazing!!!  I cannot wait to go again.
Great food,  great service 👍
My new upscale Caribbean restaurant - chef Robinson

The menu is a different twist to your regular Carribean food. I got the pineapple shrimp dish which wasn't to sure about how the flavor would be but it turned out very good. Very good spice to the dish. We had a sample of soup I guess to pass the time which turned out to be a bit on the spicy side. .We noticed other people coughing due to the spice. We also had the salmon,which turned out not to be cooked through as ordered but the dish was good as well. I was surprised glasses on the table and silverware due to covid. I would not call that very sanitary. It took at least 40 min to get our food and it was only 3 if us. .I would suggest having another cook or extra help in the kitchen.  I definitely will not visit for dinner again it was too long a wait. Maybe lunch is faster. Your tip is already included on your bill, no problem  but if your are doing that then I think you need to have top servers which I did not see. Nothing on the menu was explained,  just not the service I would expect if my tip is included.  Also the server we had was inebriated.  If I clearly saw this in one visit, management is not aware of what's going on in there own restaurant.
Excellent food!

Very disappointed. Waited over 20 minutes for drinks. Had to ask for menus. When a member of Our party politely asked when someone would could come around to take the order after It had been about 25 minutes,  The bartender made the comment that he should expect to wait since his party didn’t have reservations. In fact, we did have reservations. They appear to be shortstaffed even though the restaurant was not full. We were offered a taste of some kind of seafood soup and I inquired about the ingredients since I do not eat meat. The server could not tell me what else was in it and did not offer to go check. At least three or four times we heard the bartender complain about other staff members or other customers.  We were a large party and felt that we were an inconvenience. It is very hard for a  Restaurant to stay in business in normal times, but in a pandemic you would expect the service to be top notch to retain customers and get good word-of-mouth referrals. I was planning to bring a group of about 30 girls here for a celebration, but I have informed them all that we are picking another location because of this. I would like to go where I’m appreciated as a paying customer

Not so great am experience today with our group. Restaurant was clean and nice, but they claimed they were short staffed. I didn't see evidence of that, just a lack of direction. They were apologetic but also at times vented publicly about their frustration over how busy they were. To me that is a happy problem in our current climate. My order did not match the menu description. A biscuit was served vs a hashbrown waffle. Our party had a reservation but it took quite a while before we were even served drinks or food.
Food was good! Service was good! Drinks were good and strong! Will definitely be coming back!

Today my boyfriend and I decided to stop by Pink Salt since we were nearby. I’ve always wanted to try it! The food was great. We had an appetizer of the jerk peel & eat shrimp & 3 entree's jerk chicken, braised rabbit, and short ribs. Food was good & my margarita was tasty. At the end, reviewing check I’ve noticed a gratuity was added. I asked Megan (our waitress) did they do this for everyone. She begins to say..one tops, two tops, three tops, all tables we add gratuity (firmly). We was fine with it but just figured it should have been mentioned in the beginning (coming from a current foh team lead). Otherwise, I recommend. We shall return!

We went early on Saturday evening for an intimate birthday dinner for 3. We enjoyed the peel and eat shrimp and okra appetizers. For dinner I had the jerk chicken that was the perfect flavor! My guest enjoyed the oxtail stew with rice and cabbage. My son is 11 years old and ate the entire bowl of yellow curry shrimp!! This place is a hidden gem and will have to go back soon. We had a taste of the curry French onion soup that was delicious too.
Great food.
I've eaten at this restaurant many times and highly recommend. The food is delicious and they have great customer service. This is my go to place for caribbean food!!
The food was good.

My friend told me about this restaurant after hearing some reviews from her coworkers. Since her and I are foodies we decided to try it out. In true consumer fashion I checked the reviews as I always do before going to a new place...One of the reviews stated that the customer was in a verbal exchange with a server. Customer stated the server reminded her that she did not tip during her previous visit, and she was lucky to even be served at that point!!! It was stated that the customer requested to speak with the manager/owner and server granted request and manager/owner refused. I also read the response of the manager/owner that stated maybe their restaurant wasn't the place for them. Although taken aback by the servers behavior and the manager/owners response, I decided to take the hour trip. I made reservations ahead of time and was a bit irritated after arriving on time and the table wasn't available. After waiting a very short time we were seated. The ambiance reminded me of some of the restaurants I enjoyed back home in Brooklyn. We were greeted with a complimentary chicken soup which was quite tasty. We arrived during happy hour (which is always a treat) and ordered some very tasty cocktails. We were interested in trying various items on the menu since it was our first time. We ordered the honey jerk wings, escovich snapper ($50), and the short ribs. The food arrived in a timely fashion which was great due to neither of us had eaten prior to arrival. The wings which were accompanied with cold fries were not as good as I thought it would be. Too many flavors and too much breading. When the entree arrived, it was esthetically pleasing due to the size of the platters and food. When my plate was placed before me I was filled with disappointment. I am familiar with a more traditional escovich snapper. What I received was fish drowned in sauce (same sauce used on the wings) and smothered in okra (which I dislike) peas, and carrots. After scrapping off the okra, sauce and vegetable topping I began eating my meal. Rice and peas were not flavorful and definitely not seasoned traditionally with coconut, and spices. The cabbage on the other hand was the best part of the meal. My friend had the short ribs which were big in size (not like the picture, but not complaining) and were quite tasty. When we were finished I asked for the bill to be split. I received my portion of the bill and was surprised by the extra $12 charge. After looking closely, I realized that the extra cost was the tip. I don't recall ever having my tip added for me when less than 4 people. My friend unknowingly began to calculate the servers tip before I told her it had already been added.  ( be on the lookout.) Another disappointment for me.  Luckily the servers were very nice and accommodating. I would not recommend the fish if you're used to a more traditional style of preparation. I would recommend cocktails, maybe some appetizers, and definitely the short ribs. I did ask my friend if she would return and her response was "I would have but after hearing about the owners response to the previous customer, maybe not." I convienently forgot to share the review that I read before. I knew she wouldn't have gone if I told her!
The service and food was excellent! Great addition to the area
The food was GREAT. We had JOE as our server and he was very attentive. I'm gonna dream about this food. It is truly a hidden gem
Excellent
The ambiance is very nice and the food is excellent!!! I had the coconut curry shrimp and OMG it tasted like I was back in Jamaica!!! I’ll definitely visit again real soon 😃

Valentines day date with my wife with reservations and was disappointed we went. I counted at least 15 tables that also included a good size bar area  and their staff was probably not well suited for a full house. I only saw two waitresses and maybe 2 bartenders. Needless to say, our service was really slow. Not to put the blame on our waitress because I'm sure she had her hands full,  but between each time she came to check on us and take our orders it was far too long. The food we thought was ok. I ordered the steak with potatoes and my wife the full snapper. We don't feel the value is there for what you get. Maybe the kitchen was rushed preparing our meal. Our bill was about 130 for 2 people that just simply did not feel it was worth it. If the service was better maybe the food portion could've been overlooked. Feel bad having to write a negative review.

Fish overcooked. Staff was disorganized. Tables left unclean for long periods of time. They did not provide a drink menu because they were “out of rum and the drink menu is 90% rum” no alternate drinks were recommended. The waitress visited our table 2 times to take our order and drop off our check (only after we had to get up and request our check from the host). We wanted to love this place and support a small local minority business, unfortunately we will not be recommending this place or returning. Lastly, our waitress wore her mask around her chin the entire time  keeping her nose and mouth exposed.

The food is good but the service is HORRIBLE!!! I have never been to a restaurant where our waiter messes up our tickets and then say “Well I’m going to leave them here and then you figure it out”! Our waiter was rude from the time we sat down.
Service slow, wait staff disorganized, fish overcooked and chewy.
They were extremely busy so we decided to sit at the bar, the service was amazing and the food was even better. Definitely would be a regular if I lived around here!
The food was delicious

My wife and I had read a lot of great reviews about this new location and had decided to try it Friday night since there were offering coupons and who doesn't like saving money. We called to place an order for pick up and was told by the hostess that they do not do take out on Friday and Saturday evenings. I ask if I understood her correctly and she stated that was their policy. I guess their business is so booming they do not care to offer all potential customers the option of trying their cuisine. Unfortunately, they did not need our money or business. My wife and I have been supporting as many of our local restaurants as possible during this pandemic, and this has been the first location that has stated the do not offer take out on a Friday night, being Friday is our date night. Thank you to all other restaurants that do offer take out for those of us who are just not ready to dine indoors at this time. We will continue to support you.
I really enjoyed this spot  I am going to be regular.

This place is amazing. Our server, bartender and all around guy JoJo recommended the gumbo and wings and can I just say WOW. He did not steer us wrong. Best food. Great drinks. Amazing service JoJo!  Can’t wait to try the whole menu.

I really enjoyed the jerk shrimp tacos!! The potions were huge for lunch. The service was amazing! Free sample of their bean soup which was fantastic!!! Clean, good location, very neat and trendy atmosphere! I will definitely be going back!!

I had reservations for party of 30 at Breezy Jazzy's Club and they canceled at the lasted minute sending me text at 4:45pm the event 7:30 pm) so I called Pink Salt spoke to owner Richard Robinson at the last minute, he accommodared my party.The food was excellent great atmospheres we really all had great time..Thanks Breezy for canceling at the last minute we had better time at Pink Salt Restaurant Wine Bar
The curry chicken could've had more curry. The jerk chicken and service was awesome.
The food and drinks was wondeful.I will be back to visit.👍☺

First time here, had the shrimp & crawfish stew for an appetizer, jerk chicken & roasted red potatoes for an entree. Both were delicious, compliments to the chef. JoJo our bartender/waiter was awesome! We will definitely return.
THE BEST !! LOV THE NEW LOCATION  !! NEVER DISAPPOINTED!!
Pink salt is a unique experience, Caribbean spice, with generous portions. not the most socially distance places at this point but safe I'm sure!
My friend and I each got a cocktail and split an appetizer and an entree. It was delicious!! We got the okra and the roasted whole red snapper. We will be back.

The atmosphere was very nice and the food was absolutely fantastic, my compliments to the chef!!! The restaurant is new, obviously growing pains are to be expected. If the service improves in regards to timeliness and finer details, I expect this will be a very popular spot!
This place is devine, the aesthetic is so beautiful, oh my God, the oxtails, soups, dips seafood you name it. 👍👍💯. Did I mention the wings, Sizzling.
Great food and atmosphere
Amazing vibe .... amazing food!! The shrimp and grits is EVERYTHING! I want a bath of the sauce to swim in! If heaven has a taste, it would be the sauce! It's that serious! #getsome 🙌🙌🙌🙌😋💓

I absolutely LOVE this restaurant that recently relocated to my San Marco @pinksaltrestaurant Treat yourself to breakfast, lunch or dinner at this neighborhood gem! Make sure you try the Pink Salt signature cocktail.  You're welcome!
username: Tara Braithwaite Coldwell Banker Vanguard Realty

caption: This has quickly become my FAVORITE restaurant in Jacksonville!!!   The food is AMAZING, the Chef is OUTSTANDING, and the atmosphere is FRIENDLY & RELAXING :-)  l really enjoyed the new location.
Very good caribbean food and service

This truly is a hidden gem. Every item we had was delicious. The ambiance was so cozy and beautiful decor. The waitress Katie and Shawn were so friendly. I truly enjoyed my visit here. You will not be disappointed with any items you order. Richard the owner, came over and we had a nice chat. He is so down to earth. This is an absolutely must try. The oxtails abs ribs were so tender is fell off the bone. The fusion of flavors were off the chart.

I am speechless...but, I'll force myself to leave this review. Pink Salt is exactly what we need in Jax; the perfect pairing of top notch Caribbean food with elegance and class. The setting is perfect, the service is stellar and the food is amazing. Everything was perfectly seasoned! The presentation was beautiful. The owner is the perfect host as well. Love this place ❤. We will be back!

It’s our first time here and I would say all the meals that we ordered were flawless and made by an exemplary chef! We got the following:  Jerk Wings - honey glazed jerk wings. No need for any dip. The wings were cooked to perfection!  Jerk Chicken Bowl - for some reason, the taste reminded me of teriyaki but much, much better! Hubby definitely enjoyed it!  Jumbo Gumbo - generous portions of seafood and vegetables. It has some okra, tomatoes and bell pepper. I got it with grits since we already have rice from the chicken, but will definitely order with rice next time! All that sauce is best with rice! So rich yet not overwhelming! Such an excellent dish! My favorite so far!  We also get to try the homemade kimchi! I love kimchi and I just want to say I prefer Pink Salt’s version! Different from the original, but very, very good!  We were the first customers but I’m so glad that people started coming in after our lunch. They need our support to stay in business especially during this tumultuous time. Do visit this awesome restaurant!
Food was magnificent

I'm so happy me and my boyfriend were able to find this gem . Our server Daniel was absolutely amazing and  very accommodating The chef is very kind and knows his stuff when it comes to food I highly recommend this place to anyone looking for positive vibes  great service and excellent food! They are also moving to San Marco excited to see the new place

Daniel was a very attentive and personable waiter!! Food was awesome and well seasoned. I called my Mom from the restaurant to tell her how great it was and she ordered a to go plate! Shrimp curry sauce was so creamy and flavorful. Plantains cooked to perfection. They are moving to San Marco near Zeus Pizza!
Party in the mouth. Flavors are exquisite. Chef has a gift. This place deserves your patronage.
Wonderful friendly trendy place with happy vibes. Great decor and fun music. Food is great. Coctails are good too. Service is decent. Will definitely return soon.
Really great food!

I have not tried the food here yet, although it does look amazing,  the reason for the 5 star review is a restaurants ability to turn things around when something has gone wrong. I had an issue with an order being canceled by GrubHub and not being able to receive my order.. I am blown away at how fast I was contacted and how a bad situation can be turned around and made into a fantastic display of great customer service.  I will be ordering/visiting soon and can't wait to try the food!
This is the most amazing food I’ve had at pink salt restaurant. I ordered  the goat with curry sauce￼ and the wonderful vegetables! I felt like Chef Richard made it especially for me!

LOVE LOVE LOVE....  Today was amazing, I had the best experience at the Pink Salt. The food was delicious. I was so embarrassed by a guest that made a scene about her order not being ready, but I paid it no mind because the service received was above amazing, food exceptional, and if you plan to dine here remember everything GREAT, takes time. This place is above your standard dining experience. I encourage everyone to go.... HATS OFF TO THE CHEF AND STAFF.

Unfortunately, this review has nothing to do with the great tasting food; however, the service by Lashandra at Pink Salt Caribbean Fusion Restaurant was terrible. My daughter and I ordered a pizza and were given the estimated wait time of 20 minutes. We walked around and went to another store to make a purchase prior to picking up our pizza. We ordered the pizza at 1:40pm and then arrived at the restaurant at about 1:58pm. At around 2:10pm, I questioned about my pizza since it had not come out yet. The server informed me that pickup times are subject to how many people they are already serving in the restaurant. She then continued to say that I had the nerve to complain when I did not tip her the last time I came to the restaurant (for a pickup order). I asked her to repeat herself and she proceeded to say that I did not tip her last time nor this time for my order. I told her I did not know I had to tip for a pickup order and if she did not have an attitude then maybe she would have gotten tipped. Lashandra continued to argue with me and told me that people like me (basically my color) are the reason why chef’s do not want to serve us. I informed her it was not professional for a server to be arguing with a customer. Her defense was that the other customers in the restaurant (mainly white and about 5 people) were not looking at her but at me since I was the fool standing there arguing with her. I then asked if I could speak with a manager. She then went to the back and continued to complain about me with the chef/manager/owner. She came back and told me the manager said he had no time to come out and talk with me. At this point, I asked for a refund. She continued to argue with me. I told her that I would pray for her and that I was in ministry. She came back at me with “keep your prayers, you false Christian. Your fake Christian mask. You are a fake minister.” I corrected her and reaffirmed that I was not a minister, but I see why she is where she is at. I pointed out to her that she was acting shallow and ghetto and that I was not the person for her to be doing this to. She took about 5 minutes trying to figure out how to process my refund and, in the end, had to get the chef/manager/owner to come out and help. When he came out to help her, he did not even acknowledge me nor apologize for my situation even though he heard the whole thing. As someone with a master’s degree and work in counseling and in education I was professional enough to keep my composure even when she pointed out that I was stupid in front of everyone present. Overall, she needs to realize that even if you are from the ghetto it does not mean you need to behave as if you are from the ghetto. It is a shame to experience such a situation even from a restaurant that is owned and run by people of my same color, especially Jamaican when my father’s family come from the islands. If I were white, would she have stood there arguing with me as a paying customer?

AMAZING! AMAZING! AMAZING! Food that makes me look at life differently. The coconut curry shrimp made me fall in love with it. The shrimp pizza had an island flavor that reinvents pizza. The service is good and the staff is very friendly. Add this restaurant to your list of usuals.

This place is a taste of the Caribbean. Jamaican food made to order . The friendly staff and chef Richard always greet you with a smile and mouth watering food. If you like it mild to spicy they got it covered. Please come hungry the portions are nice sized. Everything is great.

This weekend was my first time in Jacksonville and first time trying Chickpea Curry; let me tell you Pink Salt did not disappoint! The chickpea curry was rich and savory! My partner had the oxtail stew which she said was delectable! They were seasoned well and tender!  The Customer service was warm and expeditious. The portions were more than enough for left overs, which by the way I smashed! If I’m ever back, I will be visiting for round 2!
The jerk chicken and sweet plantains were awesome!
I stumbled upon this place to support black businesses and let me tell you the food was amazingly flavorful without being too spicy or salty. I am Caribbean and this is good food right here.
Excellent food and service.  Had an office lunch here and hope to have more soon!  Delicious.

The food was amazing! I loved the glaze jerk wings & signature sauce! The drinks were great & strong as well. The service was great & the Owner came out to make sure his guest had a great experience. I will definitely be back.
Portions were plentiful, staff was VERY friendly and the food was outstanding. Looking forward to trying more items on the menu!

This place is beyond awesome!! Food is fresh and you will have to wait for fresh food , But trust me it’s welllllll worth it . Jerk wings are the best I ever had and was so crispy like !!! The curry shrimp and rice was soooo good that I took it home and I don’t really eat leftovers like that ! The service is awesome and the music gives you a welcoming feeling! Place is clean clean clean ! It smells great ! It’s a must try !! Price is fair , not to to expensive!
The food was delicious.   Great presentation and good customer service.

I did a pick up order. The service was great ! I ordered Escovitch Fish and my husband had the oxtails. My husband is from the islands and he gave his food 👍🏾👍🏾👍🏾. Everything was fresh, hot and seasoned to perfection. Its taking everything in me not to order another one. I will definitely be back.
Excellent!  Great atmosphere!  Service and food great!!  Sheena our server was the best!!!

I think the food was good, except the rice and beans were extremely dry!!! When I requested a certain waitress I wasn’t able to get the waitress! I would have waited! That was the reason for 3⭐️ Instead of 4⭐️ all though waitress and waiter that I spoke with  were nice and respectful! Overall it was a good experience!

I shared a wonderful lunch today with my son Markus visiting from Miami. We both selected “The Pink Salt Platter” it was delicious, the honey glazed jerk wings had a sweet spicy crunch to them with tender meat inside. The Coconut curry shrimp were large & tasty with a smooth coconut curry sauce. I especially requested rice & peas as a substitute to the jasmine rice, no problem to accommodate my request. My favorite was the plantains. Overall we enjoyed the meal, each others company and a special hello visit with Chef Richard. We love the new location with the easy relaxed atmosphere & light easy Caribbean music in the back ground. We will definitely be back again. Hat’s off to Chef Richard.
Great food

We're repeat satisfied customers.  Have tried many items on the menu... chicken curry calzone, Jamaican cobb salad, tofu curry... all were excellent.  Also great to see the owner working hard the kitchen!

Dinner service on Saturday night was empty. We ordered jerk chicken wings as an appetizer, and two varieties of $5 mojitos which were overfilled with ice and underfilled with mint. The watermelon mojito left a taste in my partner's mouth for the rest of the night. The wings were slathered in a thick, sweet, ketchup-based bbq sauce (think sweet baby ray's) and they were chewy. No jerk herbs or spices could be tasted through the thick layer of sauce. The fries served with the wings were krinkle fries from a bag which were soft and starchy, like they had been microwaved.  For dinner, I had a large beef rib ($23) which was partially overcooked and slathered with an eerily similar sauce to the wings, this time with added heat, but no more flavor than before. For two sides I chose rice and peas (dry and overcooked) and grilled plantains (quite tasty). My partner had curried shrimp, which was decent, but curiously did not contain rice. She did not have a choice of side item.  Overall, the dinner service was terrible for the price. I do not know about the lunch or breakfast, but I wouldn't recommend coming for dinner to any of my friends.

I ordered the island ribs and paid 23 dollars and some change and got 2 ribs that was majority FAT than meat and the so called cabbage was nothing but pre packaged cole slaw.....I might as well had throwed 23 dollars in the garbage...would have given 0 stars but had to give 1 star to post review.....and the Chef/Owner was very stand offish and NOT friendly did not even greet or speak to me just walked right pass me.....would not suggest this place to anyone and this place will not be in business long
Delicious food, and the lunch buffet was perfect for my hungry teen.

I highly recommend this restaurant, the food was delicious! I ordered the curry shrimp and it was so good I have no complaints on flavor. The only thing I will say is for it to be an entree it didnt come with much coconut milk broth. I could of used more of that to eat with the rice and fill my stomach a little more. Everything else was great.

The food was wonderful. It was fun to explore the unusual menu. The Collard Green Dip with plantains was yummy.  The Coconut Roasted Basil Soup was even more yummy.   There are vegan/vegetarian options.  The service was friendly.  I will definitely be back. This place is great!
First time going to this place today and I was impressed plus it's black owned which I support 100%!!I will defiantly be back!!!
The food is good but the wait is extremely  long.  Bring some earbuds and watch Netflix  on your phone because youre going to be here  a while. 2hrs minimum. You'll be waiting over an hour for food.
Great service. French Onion soup is awesome. Super friendly staff.
Great food - nice waitress - good fresh - so glad to have this restaurant in our neighborhood 😍

Hello Mr.  Richard, I want to apologize for leaving before receiving my food. However, I think more than an hour is too long to wait for a salad. God bless your business. I'm sure it would have been good.
Great food
Great food, nice new location

So damn GOOD !!!! I had the oxtails today and they were seasoned to perfection, not to mention so tender and fresh.  The okra appetizer is a must try... could not get enough. Bravo Chef !  ... who, by the way,  just walks around with a smile.

I've visited this fine establishment many times and can attest that the food and service have always been excellent! Receptionist Marcia immediately greets patrons as they enter and makes them feel welcome from the outset. On my 1st visit I ordered the Kale Salad and unsweet tea. The salad was delicious, nutritious, and very flavorful and the tea tasted very fresh!  Hard-working Executive Chef Richard Robinson frequently emerges from the kitchen and circulates around the restaurant talking to the patrons (including me), and asks them about their experience. The atmosphere is very open and friendly and the tables are well spaced so as to provide an enjoyable dining experience. Modern and colorful artwork adorns the walls adding to the ambiance, and there is a really cool mural on the main wall leading to the kitchen.  During my 1st visit I suggested that more Vegetarian options be added to the menu, such as a quinoa veggie burger. Following up on my suggestion a Jackfruit Quinoa Burger was added to the menu. I tried it at the Grand Opening and it was delicious and slightly spicy, just perfect all around. Also I tried the onion rings and they were delectable!  I really like this restaurant, the staff and the casual ambiance! I heartily recommend Pink Salt Restaurant to anyone who is seeking a fine dining experience for breakfast or luncheon in the Southside JAX area.  Update 01/15/2020: I attended the Grand Opening of new venue located at 5111 Baymeadows Rd. and it is awesome! Very spacious with lovely wine bar, outdoor deck, and beautiful artwork everywhere. Executive Chef Richard has added many new menu items and the fusion is unique. I tried the Veggie Calzone and my friend ordered the Jerk Chicken Pizza. Both dishes were very tasteful, the dough was chewy and flavorful, and portions were huge. You must see and experience this new restaurant and the fabulous cuisine!

From the moment I entered Pink Salt I was greeted with a genuine welcome an a bueatiful Jamaciam smile from Marcia Robinson whose cousin Richard is the chef /owner an anchors the kitchen along with  His mother. The entire dining experience an Marcia kept me smiling through out our visit my neighbor Linda an I had recently eaten at Chef Kenny Gilbert's restaurant in Jax Beach an had a wonderful pork belly we shared this with Marcia! an the personal challenge was on! an Pink Salt was the winnerThe Robisons have only been in their physical complex an old sandwich shop they converted into a vibrant upbeat Caribbean restaurant complete with s small nook library were one can compfortly be tempted to nap on the couch after a great meal. Chef Robinson is a young creative chef from Atlanta who serves fresh  traditional Caribbean  dishes our may port shrimp an grits were superb the grits perfectly cooked😊an the seafood gumbo had a great Rue that made the shrimp,susage an new potatoes  delightful eating. What a delightful experience today at Pink Salt restaurant. Chef owner Richard Robinson knows his craft. A menu stacked with Caribbean Fusion offerings found me scratching my head over which to order first. The dining room is large well-lit and the walls are covered with amazing artwork, plus there's a small room in the back for sitting and reading or trading books oh, I don't believe there's another restaurant like it in Jacksonville. Everything from Chef Robinson kitchen is scratch made and you can definitely tell the difference. One of the dishes that stood out in my mind was the Blue Crab soup. A smoothe broth, richly spiced,  that offered up large pieces of sweet Blue Crabmeat and yellow corn.  If you have an opportunity get over to Pink Salt, and meet the chef, his story is most inspiring.
